---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Cora — FAQ">

	<Navbar />

	<main>

		<!-- ===== HERO ===== -->
		<section class="hero" id="hero">
			<div class="container hero-container hero-container-wide">
				<h1 class="hero-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
				<p class="hero-sub">
					Everything you need to know about Cora&mdash;from security and pricing to technical details and error handling.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- ===== FAQ SECTIONS ===== -->
		<section class="faq-page">
			<div class="container faq-container">

				<!-- ===== SECURITY & PRIVACY ===== -->
				<div class="faq-section">
					<h2 class="faq-section-title">Security &amp; Privacy</h2>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>Is my data safe with Cora?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>Absolutely. Data security is foundational to how we built Cora:</p>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Your hardware, your data:</strong> With Cora Flex and Cora Pro, data stays on hardware you physically control. Nothing leaves your premises unless you configure it to.</li>
								<li><strong>Encryption everywhere:</strong> All data is encrypted at rest and in transit using industry-standard AES-256 and TLS 1.3.</li>
								<li><strong>No training on your data:</strong> We never use your business data to train our AI models. Your data is yours alone.</li>
								<li><strong>Regular security audits:</strong> We perform weekly security reviews and penetration testing on all systems.</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>What system access does Cora have?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>We follow the principle of minimum access. Your Cora only gets access to what it needs to do its job:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>Access is configured during onboarding based on the role you define.</li>
								<li>You can expand or restrict access at any time.</li>
								<li>Every permission change is logged and auditable.</li>
								<li>Your Cora uses your existing authentication&mdash;no special API keys that bypass your security.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>Think of it like onboarding any new employee: you decide what they can access.</p>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>Is there an audit trail of what Cora does?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>Yes. Complete audit logging is built into every Cora deployment:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>Every action is logged with timestamp, context, and outcome.</li>
								<li>You can see what your Cora did, when it did it, and why.</li>
								<li>Logs are exportable for compliance and review.</li>
								<li>Real-time activity monitoring via dashboard or Slack/Teams.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>You have more visibility into your AI employee than most managers have into their human teams.</p>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>What about compliance (security, healthcare, GDPR)?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>We take compliance seriously and designed Cora to meet enterprise requirements:</p>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Security controls:</strong> Our infrastructure and processes are built for enterprise audit readiness.</li>
								<li><strong>Healthcare compliance:</strong> For healthcare customers, we offer tailored data-handling configurations and documentation support.</li>
								<li><strong>GDPR:</strong> Full GDPR compliance including data portability and right to deletion.</li>
								<li><strong>On-premise option:</strong> Cora Flex and Cora Pro keep all data on your hardware, making compliance your responsibility and under your control.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>Need specific compliance documentation? <a href="mailto:hello@cora.st">Contact us</a>.</p>
						</div>
					</details>
				</div>

				<!-- ===== RELIABILITY & ERROR HANDLING ===== -->
				<div class="faq-section">
					<h2 class="faq-section-title">Reliability &amp; Error Handling</h2>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>What happens if the AI makes a mistake?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>AI isn't perfect, and we've built Cora with that reality in mind:</p>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Configurable guardrails:</strong> Set limits on what actions require approval (e.g., emails over a certain value, external communications).</li>
								<li><strong>Undo and rollback:</strong> Most actions can be reversed, and your Cora logs everything for easy correction.</li>
								<li><strong>Escalation paths:</strong> Configure when your Cora should stop and ask a human.</li>
								<li><strong>Learning from mistakes:</strong> When you correct your Cora, it remembers and improves.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>The goal isn't perfection&mdash;it's to be dramatically better than the alternative (work not getting done, or hiring and training humans).</p>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>What's the uptime guarantee?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>Uptime depends on your deployment model:</p>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Cora Cloud:</strong> 99.9% uptime SLA with automatic failover and redundancy.</li>
								<li><strong>Cora Flex / Cora Pro:</strong> Hardware uptime depends on your environment. The software is designed to auto-recover from crashes and network interruptions.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>Your Cora also continues working through brief connectivity issues by queueing actions and syncing when reconnected.</p>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>How does error handling work?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>When your Cora encounters an error or unexpected situation:</p>
							<ol>
								<li><strong>Automatic retry:</strong> For transient errors (API timeouts, network blips), it retries intelligently.</li>
								<li><strong>Alternative approaches:</strong> If one method fails, it tries other ways to accomplish the goal.</li>
								<li><strong>Escalation:</strong> If it can't resolve the issue, it notifies you via your preferred channel (Slack, email, SMS).</li>
								<li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Every error is logged with full context for review.</li>
							</ol>
							<p>You can configure how aggressive vs. cautious you want error handling to be.</p>
						</div>
					</details>
				</div>

				<!-- ===== COMMON QUESTIONS ===== -->
				<div class="faq-section">
					<h2 class="faq-section-title">Common Questions</h2>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>How is this different from ChatGPT?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>ChatGPT is a chatbot. Cora is an employee. The difference is fundamental:</p>
							<p><strong>ChatGPT:</strong> Answers questions when asked. Requires constant prompting. Can't take actions in the real world. Forgets context between sessions. No access to your systems.</p>
							<p><strong>Cora:</strong> Works proactively without prompting. Takes actions: sends emails, updates systems. Remembers everything about your business. Accesses your actual tools and data. Runs 24/7 on dedicated hardware.</p>
							<p>Think of ChatGPT as a smart assistant you talk to. Cora is an employee who does work.</p>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>Can I control what Cora does?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>You have complete control. Cora is designed with control as a core principle:</p>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Approval workflows:</strong> Require human approval for specific action types.</li>
								<li><strong>Access controls:</strong> Define exactly which systems and data it can access.</li>
								<li><strong>Time boundaries:</strong> Set when it can/can't work or contact people.</li>
								<li><strong>Spending limits:</strong> Cap financial actions or require approval above thresholds.</li>
								<li><strong>Kill switch:</strong> Pause or stop your Cora instantly from any device.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>Start conservative and expand permissions as trust builds&mdash;just like with any new hire.</p>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>What if I want to stop using Cora?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>You can cancel anytime with no penalties:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>Month-to-month billing, cancel anytime.</li>
								<li>All your data is exported before termination.</li>
								<li>For hardware options, you have the option to keep or return the device.</li>
								<li>No lock-in contracts or cancellation fees.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>We want you to stay because Cora delivers value, not because you're trapped.</p>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>Isn't AI going to replace all jobs?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>Cora isn't about replacing your team&mdash;it's about augmenting their capacity:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>Your existing team can focus on high-value, creative, strategic work.</li>
								<li>Tasks that weren't getting done now get done.</li>
								<li>Coverage gaps (nights, weekends, holidays) are filled.</li>
								<li>New hires can be delayed or avoided entirely.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>Most customers use Cora to handle work that was either falling through the cracks or required hiring someone they couldn't justify.</p>
						</div>
					</details>
				</div>

				<!-- ===== TECHNICAL QUESTIONS ===== -->
				<div class="faq-section">
					<h2 class="faq-section-title">Technical Questions</h2>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>What systems can Cora access?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>Cora can work with virtually any software that a human can use:</p>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Web apps:</strong> CRMs (Salesforce, HubSpot), support tools (Zendesk, Intercom), project management (Asana, Monday), and more.</li>
								<li><strong>Desktop apps:</strong> Excel, Word, QuickBooks, design tools, IDEs.</li>
								<li><strong>Email:</strong> Gmail, Outlook, or any IMAP/SMTP provider.</li>
								<li><strong>Communication:</strong> Slack, Teams, Discord&mdash;your Cora can be messaged directly.</li>
								<li><strong>APIs:</strong> Direct integrations for faster, more reliable automation.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>If there's a specific tool you need, ask us&mdash;we probably already support it.</p>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>How does Cora learn my workflows?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>Your Cora learns through a combination of methods:</p>
							<ol>
								<li><strong>Initial onboarding:</strong> We document your processes, tools, and preferences during setup.</li>
								<li><strong>Observation:</strong> Your Cora can watch you work and learn patterns.</li>
								<li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Upload SOPs, guides, or training materials for instant learning.</li>
								<li><strong>Feedback loops:</strong> When you correct or guide your Cora, it adapts.</li>
								<li><strong>Continuous improvement:</strong> Every night, your Cora reviews its performance and optimizes.</li>
							</ol>
							<p>Within a week, most deployments are operating at near-full capacity for their defined role.</p>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>Can Cora work with my existing tools?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>Yes&mdash;that's the point. Unlike tools that require you to change your workflow:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>Cora works within your existing tool stack.</li>
								<li>No new software for your team to learn.</li>
								<li>No migrations or data exports required.</li>
								<li>Your Cora logs into tools like any employee would.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>If a human can do it on a computer, your Cora can do it.</p>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>What hardware specs are included?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>Hardware varies by plan:</p>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Cora Cloud:</strong> Dedicated VPS, 8GB RAM, 4 vCPUs, Scalable storage.</li>
								<li><strong>Cora Flex:</strong> Mac Mini M2, 16GB RAM, 256GB SSD, Your network.</li>
								<li><strong>Cora Pro:</strong> Mac Pro / Studio, 64GB+ RAM, 1TB+ SSD, Local AI models.</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
					</details>
				</div>

				<!-- ===== PRICING & BILLING ===== -->
				<div class="faq-section">
					<h2 class="faq-section-title">Pricing &amp; Billing</h2>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>What's included with every plan?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>Every Cora plan includes comprehensive onboarding and ongoing support:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>Up to 50 hours of onboarding and setup.</li>
								<li>Weekly one hour calls for the first year.</li>
								<li>Workflow design and iteration.</li>
								<li>Guidance on permissions and access.</li>
								<li>Monitoring, tuning, and troubleshooting.</li>
								<li>Ongoing performance management.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>Think of this as hiring an employee with a dedicated manager, not installing software.</p>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>Can I cancel anytime?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>Yes, absolutely. No contracts, no cancellation fees:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>Month-to-month billing.</li>
								<li>Cancel with 30 days notice.</li>
								<li>Data export provided before termination.</li>
								<li>For hardware plans: option to purchase the device or return it.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>We're confident you'll want to stay, but you're never locked in.</p>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>Are there any hidden fees?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>No hidden fees. Your monthly price includes:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>Hardware (for Cora Flex/Pro) or cloud infrastructure (Cora Cloud).</li>
								<li>All software and AI model costs.</li>
								<li>Onboarding, setup, and ongoing support.</li>
								<li>Automatic updates and improvements.</li>
								<li>Weekly calls for the first year.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>Pricing reflects both the AI employee and the ongoing service required to make it effective.</p>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>Do you offer discounts for annual billing?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>Yes! Annual billing includes a 15% discount:</p>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Cora Flex:</strong> $3,000/mo &rarr; $2,550/mo (annual).</li>
								<li><strong>Cora Pro:</strong> $5,000/mo &rarr; $4,250/mo (annual).</li>
								<li><strong>Cora Cloud:</strong> $3,000/mo &rarr; $2,550/mo (annual).</li>
							</ul>
							<p><a href="mailto:hello@cora.st">Contact us</a> for annual billing options.</p>
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary class="faq-question">
							<span>How does Cora compare to hiring a full-time employee?</span>
							<svg class="faq-chevron" width="12" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1.5l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>Most customers compare Cora to a full-time hire, not a SaaS subscription:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>No recruiting, interviewing, or onboarding delays.</li>
								<li>Works 24/7 without overtime or burnout.</li>
								<li>Expert-level execution across multiple domains.</li>
								<li>No benefits, taxes, or HR overhead.</li>
								<li>Scales up or down without severance.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>Cora is a managed AI employee&mdash;the pricing reflects both the technology and the ongoing service required to make it valuable.</p>
						</div>
					</details>
				</div>

			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- ===== FINAL CTA ===== -->
		<section class="section final-cta" id="final-cta">
			<div class="container final-cta-container">
				<h2 class="final-cta-heading">Still Have Questions?</h2>
				<p class="final-cta-sub">
					We're happy to walk you through anything. Reach out and we'll get back to you within 24 hours.
				</p>
				<a href="mailto:hello@cora.st" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Contact Us &rsaquo;</a>
			</div>
		</section>

	</main>

	<Footer />

</Layout>
